predict_diagnosis:
1. Ovarian cancer
2. Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)
3. Germ cell tumors
4. Sex chromosome abnormalities (Turner syndrome, Klinefelter syndrome, etc.)
5. Congenital adrenal hyperplasia (CAH)
6. Congenital skeletal abnormalities
7. Hypothyroidism
8. Hyperparathyroidism
9. Hormonal imbalances due to endocrine tumors
10. Cushing's syndrome

It is important to note that all of these diagnoses have overlapping symptoms and may require further testing, such as imaging, biopsy, and hormonal testing, to confirm the diagnosis.
